<h2 id=3D"id-08.SD:InterestandTaxSummary-RAID-Risk,Assumptions,IssuesandDep=
endencies">RAID - Risk, Assumptions, Issues and Dependencies</h2>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"id-08.SD:InterestandTaxSummary-Assumptions">Assumptions</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<thead class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th class=3D"highlight-#f4f5f7 confluenceTh" style=3D"text-align: left;vert=
ical-align: top;" data-highlight-colour=3D"#f4f5f7"><p>Ref #</p></th>
<th class=3D"highlight-#f4f5f7 confluenceTh" style=3D"text-align: left;vert=
ical-align: top;" data-highlight-colour=3D"#f4f5f7"><p>Assumption</p></th>
<th class=3D"highlight-#f4f5f7 confluenceTh" style=3D"text-align: left;vert=
ical-align: top;" data-highlight-colour=3D"#f4f5f7"><p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A01</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Interest and tax summary CAP API will be Instl Account Transaction compo=
nent (<a href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/instl-account-=
transactions-v1" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">instl-account-tra=
nsactions-v1 - APIs - Components - Mesh Connect</a>) -&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>On Interest and tax summary page, the downstream&nbsp;CAP API which the =
EXP API is getting data from is the Instl Account Transaction component (<a=
 href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/instl-account-transact=
ions-v1" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">instl-account-transaction=
s-v1 - APIs - Components - Mesh Connect</a>)</p>
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-29" class=3D"date-past">29 May 2025</time>&nbs=
p; Having a discussion with ATLAS / Account / workflow squad, it's aligned =
that most data will be coming from Entitlement and ATLAS. We won't need an =
extra CAP layer to handle data aggregation from ATLAS and 10x.</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A02</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>10x should holds more than 3 years of account detail record even if the =
account is closed. <strong>(BR.03)</strong></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
10x should at least holds 3 years of core account record, even account has =
been closed, to fulfil the captured requirement. (i.e. everything that is c=
oming from 10x, e.g. Account status, Credit interest rate (account level), =
Interest rate type (account level), Interest rate structure (account level)=
,&nbsp;<span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Interest accrual cycle (accou=
nt level)</span></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A03</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Instl Account Transaction CAP API aggregates data from 10x and ATLAS.</p=
></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>Account core information should be from10x (including account/product le=
vel interest rate) and transaction related information should be retrieved =
from ATLAS (e.g. interest paid / interest earned), and it's served by Instl=
 Account Transaction CAP API which combines the data.&nbsp;</p>
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-29" class=3D"date-past">29 May 2025</time>&nbs=
p; As discussed with Andrew, we won't need an extra CAP layer to handle dat=
a aggregation from ATLAS and 10x. Account-level filtering will be handled b=
y the newly introduced "Account Utility API".</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A04</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Channel / Instl Account Transaction component can source the Account nam=
e from ATLAS.&nbsp;<strong> (BR.01 /&nbsp;BR.04)</strong></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>For the account name displayed on the tax and summary page, it has been =
confirmed with the business that it matches the name obtained from another =
account listing screen, which is sourced from the 10x Account API. Assume t=
he account name can be retrieved from ATLAS.</p>
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-29" class=3D"date-past">29 May 2025</time> &nb=
sp;Get the recommendation from <a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention=
" data-username=3D"M058573" href=3D"/display/~M058573" data-linked-resource=
-id=3D"1125291984" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-=
type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">A=
ve Cahyadi</a> we will rely on the account name retrieved from Entitlement.=
&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A05</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Data for non-interest-bearing account will not be available in ATLAS <st=
rong>(BR.03)</strong></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>As discussed with @Sam and @Umesh, an ATLAS feature to be delivered in N=
ovember <em>(JIRA-ID)</em> will calculate and store interest only for inter=
est-bearing accounts. If no data is received from ATLAS for an account, we =
can assume the account is non-interest bearing.</p>
<p><img height=3D"150" style=3D"margin: 2px; border: 1px solid #ddd; box-si=
zing: border-box; vertical-align: text-bottom;" src=3D"fdec9634bac2d3d28b8b=
c68cba5a169073a84fa4eedbe6fa1d90720f7183f36d" width=3D"150"></p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A06</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Data for closed account will not be available in ATLAS. <strong>(BR.08)<=
/strong></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>As discussed with @Sam and @Umesh, if the account is closed, no interest=
 or tax information will be available in ATLAS. We can assume the account i=
s either closed or non-interest bearing if no data is available in ATLAS. A=
s long as the account is open at any point within the current year, we shou=
ld receive interest and tax data from ATLAS for the account.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"id-08.SD:InterestandTaxSummary-Constraints&amp;Dependencies">Cons=
traints &amp; Dependencies</h3>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 364.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 372.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 480.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 361.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 184.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Ref #</st=
rong></p><p>[C-###, D-###]</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Considera=
tions Type</strong></p><p>[Constraints, Dependencies]</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Descripti=
on</strong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Notes</st=
rong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Date</str=
ong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C-ART-14409-001</=
p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Constraint</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">GCM doesn't support =
bulk query, and it may affect the performance of the API if WASH API is doi=
ng the aggregation.&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>Per discussion with <a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-u=
sername=3D"M061387" href=3D"/display/~M061387" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1=
359044573" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"=
userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Thomas Va=
n Deun</a> it's the current constraint with WASH API</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-06" class=3D"date-past">06 May 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C-ART-14409-002</=
p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Constraint</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>To maximize the r=
e-use of existing capability, re-use of the Account detail API is proposed.=
 (cap<a href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/cap-prodsvcadm-=
proddealacctadm-instl-arrngmntsvcng-v1?tab=3Dcontract" class=3D"external-li=
nk" rel=3D"nofollow">-prodsvcadm-proddealacctadm-instl-arrngmntsvcng-v1 - A=
PIs - Components - Mesh&nbsp;</a>Connect)</p><p>Yet it's getting single acc=
ount information from 10x and GCM.<br>
 if data retrieval in bulk is required either we will need to loop this API=
 calls for X times or a new capability need to be introduced.&nbsp;</p></td=
>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>If we decide to re-use the existing capability potentially it may cause =
performance impact.&nbsp;<br>
 For a single API at the CAP layer, it's costing around 500-600ms today.&nb=
sp;</p>
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-20" class=3D"date-past">20 May 2025</time> Dis=
cussed with Account team Nick confirms that data on Tax and Interest summar=
y page can be retrieved from ATLAS</p>
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-21" class=3D"date-past">21 May 2025</time> Dis=
cussed with ATLAS team data from ATLAS can help to determine if the account=
 is closed and non-interest bearing. (see assumption A05/A06). Also, the ac=
count name can be retrieved from ATLAS if it's sourced from 10x. (see assum=
ption A04)</p>
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-29" class=3D"date-past">29 May 2025</time> Acc=
ount name will be sourced from Entitlement. ( see comments from A04)</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-14" class=3D"date-past">14 May 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>D-JIRAFEATURE-00X=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Dependency</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"id-08.SD:InterestandTaxSummary-KeyDecisions"><span>Key Decisions<=
/span></h2>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped relative-table confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 94.=
9084%;">
<thead class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Ref #</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Decision</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Description</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Decision made by</span></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Date</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 3.10142%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 16.2537%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 60.3655%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 12.7503%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 7.52382%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
#001</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Decision on the maximum page size supported for every request</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>As discussed previously, for each request to the Instl Account Transacti=
on component and its downstream systems (e.g., ATLAS DynamoDB), we must con=
sider both the actual account volume and the performance of the downstream =
APIs when determining the maximum number of records to return.</p>
<p>The next step is to collect real production data to understand the numbe=
r of accounts customers have. This will help us agree on a number that bala=
nces business needs and performance.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-29" class=3D"date-past">29 May 2025</time> Dat=
a will be coming from ATLAS mainly and confirmed with <a class=3D"confluenc=
e-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"L203394" href=3D"/display/~L20339=
4" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1924200158" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1=
" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://confluenc=
e.srv.westpac.com.au">Unknown User (l203394)</a> the required page size can=
 be supported.&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M061387" =
href=3D"/display/~M061387" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1359044573" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Thomas Van Deun</a> <a class=
=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"L203394" href=3D"/di=
splay/~L203394" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1924200158" data-linked-resource=
-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"http=
s://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Unknown User (l203394)</a>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M064489" =
href=3D"/display/~M064489" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1920714325" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Edmond Tso</a> <a class=3D"co=
nfluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M062050" href=3D"/display/=
~M062050" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1515690289" data-linked-resource-versi=
on=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://co=
nfluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Andrew Suduk</a>&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-05" class=3D"date-past">05 May 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
#002&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Decision on the batching of API request</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><strong>Problem Statement</strong></p>
<p>The current implementation of the <strong>GTS INF API</strong> imposes a=
 <strong>limitation of 100 accounts per request</strong>. This constraint e=
xists because the statement that <strong>each account triggers a separate c=
all to DynamoDB</strong>, resulting in significant load and potential perfo=
rmance bottlenecks.</p>
<p><strong>Discussion</strong></p>
<p>There is an ongoing conversation about <strong>increasing the limit to 3=
00 accounts</strong> for the <strong>November release</strong>.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Andrew Suduk</strong> will collaborate with <strong>Jolly</stro=
ng> to <strong>validate the performance impact</strong> of this change.</li=
>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p>If performance testing shows <strong>no adverse impact</strong>, the lim=
it will be <strong>temporarily increased to 300 accounts</strong> for Novem=
ber.</p>
<p>This will remain in place <strong>until a strategic architectural decisi=
on</strong> is made on how to handle multi-account requests more efficientl=
y. One proposed direction from Ave is to:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Query data by a single organization ID</strong>&nbsp;rather tha=
n querying by a list of account IDs.</li>
</ul>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M058573" =
href=3D"/display/~M058573" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1125291984" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Ave Cahyadi</a>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M064401" =
href=3D"/display/~M064401" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1309836187" data-link=
